@startuml object-watermark
'' ============================================================================
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this is an OBJECT/COMPONENT pipeline showing
'' how the Vinary Tree logo SVG is rendered as a faint, grayscale watermark.
'' Mermaid has no first-class object diagram with typed compartments and per-object
'' fill colors; PlantUML's `rectangle`+`card` with inline per-element colors lets
'' each stage carry the palette color of the concept it belongs to (filesystem
'' asset, IPC-less renderer CSS, final rendered emblem).
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Watermark emblem pipeline — vinary-tree-logo.svg → <img> + grayscale filter → faint logo

'' ---- the source asset (filesystem / static resource = tan) ----
rectangle "vinary-tree-logo.svg\n(resources/public/assets)" as SVG FS_FILL {
  card "the full-color Vinary Tree crest\n(heraldic shield + tree-of-life\n+ 'VINARY TREE' wordmark)" as SVGBODY #FBF8EF
}

'' ---- the renderer markup + CSS that fades it to a watermark (renderer = teal) ----
rectangle ".vv-watermark-logo  <img>  (views.cljs + app.css)" as IMG RENDERER_FILL {
  card "<img src=\"assets/vinary-tree-logo.svg\">\ncentered by .vv-watermark (flex)" as TAG #FBF8EF
  card "width: 40%; max-width: 360px\nheight: auto" as SIZE #FBF8EF
  card "filter : grayscale(1)\nopacity: 0.08" as FADE #FBF8EF
}

'' ---- the rendered result inside the empty content pane ----
rectangle "rendered emblem\n.vv-watermark > img.vv-watermark-logo" as OUT #1F6B53 {
  card "a faint, desaturated\nVinary Tree logo,\ncentered in the empty tab" as EMBLEM #FBF8EF
}

'' ---- wiring (each arrow is one rendering step) ----
SVG -[#6F5E47,thickness=2]-> IMG : (1) loaded as an <img>\n(its own colors, drawn as-is)
IMG -[#1F6B53,thickness=2]-> OUT : (2) desaturated by grayscale(1)\nand faded to 8% opacity

note bottom of OUT
  The watermark is **theme-independent**: the logo is desaturated and faded by CSS,
  so it reads the same faint grayscale in every theme. (The earlier CSS-mask design —
  ADR-0007 — tinted a monochrome shield.svg with --vv-fg; it was superseded by this
  full-color logo, and shield.svg is now orphaned.)
end note

legend right
  |= color |= concept |
  |<#9F8766>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| filesystem / static SVG asset |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| renderer (Chromium) markup + CSS — no IPC, paint-only |
  |<#1F6B53>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| final rendered emblem |
endlegend
@enduml
